<!-- §9 What is a scalp massager with red light -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is a Scalp Massager with Red Light Therapy?</h2>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A scalp massager with red light therapy is a handheld device that combines vibration therapy with light-based wellness technology. The vibration component uses a motor to create rapid, rhythmic movements that stimulate the scalp and promote blood circulation. The red light component emits wavelengths (typically 600–700 nanometers) marketed to support cellular health and hair growth.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">This particular model uses a rechargeable battery, detachable comb head for easy cleaning, and USB charging for convenience. The motor power ranges from 4.7–8.6W depending on intensity level, delivering noticeable vibration strength. The red light activates simultaneously with the massage, creating a multi-sensory wellness experience.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">Scalp massage therapy has long been valued in traditional wellness practices for promoting relaxation and circulation. Adding red light is a modern twist that appeals to those interested in biohacking and preventive health. However, it's important to note that while massage quality is immediate and tangible, red light therapy claims for hair growth remain scientifically limited at the consumer-device level.</p>

