<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Does the red light therapy actually help with hair growth?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Red light therapy shows promise in professional-grade clinical studies, but evidence at consumer-device levels is limited. Most validated studies use specialized equipment in dermatology clinics, not handheld home devices. This device's red light is likely beneficial for scalp circulation and general wellness, but don't rely on it as a proven hair loss treatment. Use the massage function as your primary benefit; treat red light as a bonus wellness feature.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How long does the battery last on a full charge?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The 1200mAh battery typically provides 1–2 hours of continuous use, depending on which intensity level you're running. Most people use the device for 10–15 minute sessions daily, so you'll likely charge it 2–3 times per week. Full recharge takes about 2–3 hours via the USB cable.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I adjust the vibration intensity?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes. Most models feature 3–5 intensity levels. Start with the lowest setting to let your scalp adjust, then gradually increase. The 4.7–8.6W motor range means there's significant customization available. This is important for sensitive scalps or if you're new to scalp massage.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Is it safe to use on wet hair?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The device is water-resistant but not fully waterproof. Use it on dry or damp hair, not dripping wet. Avoid using it in the shower or immediately after washing. The detachable comb head is easy to rinse clean with water if needed, but the motor unit should stay dry. Always check your specific device's waterproof rating before exposing it to moisture.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How does this compare to the Electric Scalp Massager ($62)?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The Rechargeable Scalp Massager Comb ($85.53, Vibe Score 74) includes red light therapy, higher motor power (4.7–8.6W), and a rechargeable battery. The Electric Scalp Massager ($62, Vibe Score 71) focuses purely on massage quality without red light. If you value red light and rechargeable convenience, choose the premium model. If you want excellent massage at a better price, the $62 model is still outstanding.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">What comes in the box?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Rechargeable Scalp Massager Comb unit, USB charging cable, detachable comb head, instruction manual, and sometimes a carrying case depending on your variant. Batteries are not required. Available in White, Black, and Emerald colors.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Will this help with my hair loss?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The massage can improve scalp circulation, which supports overall scalp health. However, this is not a hair loss treatment. For significant hair loss, consult a dermatologist. This device is best used as a wellness tool to complement your routine and support healthy scalp conditions.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How loud is the vibration?</summary>
